HEADWORD: Receivedness
<hw>Re*ceiv"ed*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or quality of
being received, accepted, or current; <as>as, the <ex>receivedness</ex>
of an opinion</as>.</def> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

